<li><strong>What is Amateur Radio?</strong> Amateur radio is a hobby and public service where licensed operators use radio frequencies for communication, experimentation, and emergency support.</li>

<li><strong>Technician License</strong> is the entry level license. The exam contains 35 multiple choice questions and you must answer 26 correctly to pass.</li>

